INTERPRETIVE TRACEABILITY, REPRODUCIBILITY & DRIFT GOVERNANCE
(AI Strategy Layer — Deterministic Contract)

9.4.0 Purpose & Scope
This section defines the binding, deterministic contract governing:
• Interpretive output reproducibility
 • Clause lineage integrity
 • Confidence enum binding (9.2)
 • Structural order compliance (7.8)
 • Dual-branch causality handling
 • Ambiguity categorization
 • Drift detection inputs (F-6.5.16)
 • Founder audit replay capability
 • Non-mutation guarantees
This section does NOT redefine:
• User-facing tone (7.2)
 • Structural communication order (7.8)
 • Confidence semantics (9.2)
 • Permissioning and ledger immutability (8.4)
 • Stress test definitions (15.0 / 15.1)
It binds those layers into enforceable architecture.

9.4.1 Core Determinism Doctrine
Every interpretive output must be:
Clause-bound
 Policy-hash-bound
 Model-version-bound
 Constraints-profile-bound
 Replayable
 Indexable
 Immutable
Interpretive logic must never:
• Collapse alternate branches silently
 • Mutate historical outputs
 • Drift structurally without detection
 • Present probabilistic inference

