9.4.5 Causality Handling — Dual-Branch Doctrine
When:
causality_status = UNKNOWN
System must:
1.Evaluate at least two internal branches.

2.Log both branches.

3.Present neutral dependency framing externally.

Required ITR Fields
dual_branch_evaluation: boolean

branch_A:
   assumed_causality_type
   structural_alignment_category
   confidence_enum

branch_B:
   assumed_causality_type
   structural_alignment_category
   confidence_enum

active_user_presented_path:
   NEUTRAL_DEPENDENCY_PRESENTATION | BRANCH_A | BRANCH_B
Rules:
• dual_branch_evaluation must be true for UNKNOWN causality.
 • active_user_presented_path defaults to NEUTRAL_DEPENDENCY_PRESENTATION.
 • No silent collapse permitted.
Stress validation required under Section 15 surge scenario.

